2.1 Data Collection (Progress: 30%)

2.1.1 Web Scraping TCM Textbooks and Websites Using Python

Example script:

Code 
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import pandas as pd
import time

headers = {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0"}
base_url = "https://www.zenheart.com.tw/"
meridian_urls = [f"{base_url}Meridian{str(i).zfill(2)}.php" for i in range(1, 15)]

all_acupoints = []

def extract_zhuzhi(html):
    soup = BeautifulSoup(html, 'html.parser')
    for p in soup.find_all('p'):
        if p.get_text(strip=True) == "主治":
            container_div = p.find_parent('div')
            if container_div:
                h3 = container_div.find('h3')
                if h3:
                    return h3.get_text(strip=True)
    return None

def get_acupoint_name(soup):
    h2 = soup.find("h2", class_="h1 u-heading-v7__title")
    return h2.get_text(strip=True) if h2 else ""

for meridian_url in meridian_urls:
    try:
        res = requests.get(meridian_url, headers=headers)
        res.encoding = 'utf-8'
        soup = BeautifulSoup(res.text, 'html.parser')

        links = soup.find_all("a", href=True)
        acupoint_links = [
            base_url + link["href"]
            for link in links if "Meridian" in link["href"] and "_" in link["href"]
        ]
        acupoint_links = list(set(acupoint_links))

        for acupoint_url in acupoint_links:
            try:
                r = requests.get(acupoint_url, headers=headers)
                r.encoding = 'utf-8'
                acupoint_html = r.text
                s = BeautifulSoup(acupoint_html, 'html.parser')

                zhuzhi = extract_zhuzhi(acupoint_html)
                name = get_acupoint_name(s)

                all_acupoints.append({
                    "Acupoint Name": name,
                    "URL": acupoint_url,
                    "Indications": zhuzhi
                })
                time.sleep(0.3)

            except Exception as e:
                continue

    except Exception as e:
        continue

df = pd.DataFrame(all_acupoints)
df.to_csv("zenheart_acupoints.csv", index=False, encoding='utf-8-sig')

2.2 Importing Excel File into PostgreSQL (Trial)

  • Set up connections: to connect to local SQL database
  • Imported meridian and acupoint data into PostgreSQL

Example script:

Code 
library(readxl)
library(DBI)
library(RPostgres)

acupoint <- read_excel("TCMtest01.xlsx", sheet = "Acupoint")
meridian <- read_excel("TCMtest01.xlsx", sheet = "Meridian")

con <- dbConnect(
  RPostgres::Postgres(),
  dbname = "TCMtest01",
  host = "localhost",
  port = 5432,
  user = "postgres",
  password = "Ting87724$"
)

dbExecute(con, "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS Acupoint;")
dbExecute(con, "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS Meridian;")

dbExecute(con, "
  CREATE TABLE meridian (
    meridian_code VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,
    meridian_eng VARCHAR,
    meridian_chi VARCHAR
  );
")

dbExecute(con, "
  CREATE TABLE acupoint (
    acupoint_code VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,
    acupoint_eng VARCHAR,
    acupoint_chi VARCHAR,
    body_acu VARCHAR,
    indication VARCHAR,
    function VARCHAR,
    meridian_code VARCHAR REFERENCES Meridian(meridian_code),
    location_chi VARCHAR,
    location_ima VARCHAR
  );
")

meridian <- meridian[, !names(meridian) %in% "m_ID"]
acupoint <- acupoint[, !names(acupoint) %in% "a_ID"]

dbWriteTable(con, "meridian", meridian, append = TRUE, row.names = FALSE)
dbWriteTable(con, "acupoint", acupoint, append = TRUE, row.names = FALSE)
dbDisconnect(con)

### Web Scraping TCM Textbooks and Websites Using Python

Example script:

```{python}
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import pandas as pd
import time

headers = {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0"}
base_url = "https://www.zenheart.com.tw/"
meridian_urls = [f"{base_url}Meridian{str(i).zfill(2)}.php" for i in range(1, 15)]

all_acupoints = []

def extract_zhuzhi(html):
    soup = BeautifulSoup(html, 'html.parser')
    for p in soup.find_all('p'):
        if p.get_text(strip=True) == "主治":
            container_div = p.find_parent('div')
            if container_div:
                h3 = container_div.find('h3')
                if h3:
                    return h3.get_text(strip=True)
    return None

def get_acupoint_name(soup):
    h2 = soup.find("h2", class_="h1 u-heading-v7__title")
    return h2.get_text(strip=True) if h2 else ""

for meridian_url in meridian_urls:
    try:
        res = requests.get(meridian_url, headers=headers)
        res.encoding = 'utf-8'
        soup = BeautifulSoup(res.text, 'html.parser')

        links = soup.find_all("a", href=True)
        acupoint_links = [
            base_url + link["href"]
            for link in links if "Meridian" in link["href"] and "_" in link["href"]
        ]
        acupoint_links = list(set(acupoint_links))

        for acupoint_url in acupoint_links:
            try:
                r = requests.get(acupoint_url, headers=headers)
                r.encoding = 'utf-8'
                acupoint_html = r.text
                s = BeautifulSoup(acupoint_html, 'html.parser')

                zhuzhi = extract_zhuzhi(acupoint_html)

                all_acupoints.append({
                    "Acupoint Name": name,
                    "URL": acupoint_url,
                    "Indications": zhuzhi
                })
                time.sleep(0.3)

            except Exception as e:
                continue

    except Exception as e:
        continue

df.to_csv("zenheart_acupoints.csv", index=False, encoding='utf-8-sig')
```

## Importing Excel File into PostgreSQL (Trial)

-   Set up `connections`: to connect to local SQL database\
-   Imported meridian and acupoint data into PostgreSQL

Example script:

```{r}
library(readxl)
library(DBI)
library(RPostgres)

acupoint <- read_excel("TCMtest01.xlsx", sheet = "Acupoint")
meridian <- read_excel("TCMtest01.xlsx", sheet = "Meridian")

con <- dbConnect(
  RPostgres::Postgres(),
  dbname = "TCMtest01",
  host = "localhost",
  port = 5432,
  user = "postgres",
  password = "Ting87724$"
)

dbExecute(con, "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS Acupoint;")
dbExecute(con, "DROP TABLE IF EXISTS Meridian;")

dbExecute(con, "
  CREATE TABLE meridian (
    meridian_code VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,
    meridian_eng VARCHAR,
    meridian_chi VARCHAR
  );
")

dbExecute(con, "
  CREATE TABLE acupoint (
    acupoint_code VARCHAR PRIMARY KEY,
    acupoint_eng VARCHAR,
    acupoint_chi VARCHAR,
    body_acu VARCHAR,
    indication VARCHAR,
    function VARCHAR,
    meridian_code VARCHAR REFERENCES Meridian(meridian_code),
    location_chi VARCHAR,
    location_ima VARCHAR
  );
")

meridian <- meridian[, !names(meridian) %in% "m_ID"]
acupoint <- acupoint[, !names(acupoint) %in% "a_ID"]

dbWriteTable(con, "meridian", meridian, append = TRUE, row.names = FALSE)
dbWriteTable(con, "acupoint", acupoint, append = TRUE, row.names = FALSE)
dbDisconnect(con)
```
